Rewrite rocm_attn_prefill_raw_heads_kernel to wave-parallel (13% wall, no weights)

STATUS: open. Biggest engineering-only lever for prefill.

CONTEXT: rocm_attn_prefill_raw_heads_kernel (ds4_rocm.c ~line 6552) is
the hot kernel behind ds4_metal_attention_prefill_raw_heads_tensor.
22 calls/prefill at 13.8 ms/call = 13.26% of total prefill wall.

It uses CPU-style serial scans:
  for each thread i (0..n_kv): serial dot of head_dim=512 per K row
Grid = (n_tokens, n_head). Block = 128 threads.
No FA, no wave-parallel reduction, no Q LDS staging.

DS4_N_HEAD_DIM=512 -> 512 serial FMAs per K row per thread.  Wave-parallel
would drop this to 16 FMAs + wave-shuffle reduce = >10x VALU.  At
>97% MemUnitBusy on other attention kernels, the bottleneck mix here is
likely different — measure with rocprofv3 PMC first.

